Growing urbanization and increasing exposure to noise pollution are major factors supporting market growth. Rising traffic congestion, expanding industrial activities, crowded public transportation, construction work, and densely populated cities have significantly increased everyday noise exposure. Continuous exposure to excessive noise is associated with hearing fatigue, stress, sleep disturbances, reduced productivity, and long-term hearing damage. As consumers become more aware of these health concerns, demand for comfortable, reusable, and effective hearing protection products continues to increase.
